Defendant James A Allen in court, in custody, with attorney Jeremy J Guza.   Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to counts 1 and 2 as charged in the Amended Information. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was given the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Attend Domestic Violence counseling
*No contact with:  the victim or her residence
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

COURT COSTS: on each count  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE: on each count  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DOMESTIC ABUSE SURCHARGE:  on each count $100.00 (to be paid as condition of probation)

Defendant to be given 124 days credit if revoked
